node.text:
Sharon Quirk-Silva was interviewed outside of Disneyland today. She shared her thoughts about the Governors decision not to allow theme parks such as Disneyland to reopen until the county has reached the yellow tier. I wasn’t sure if my iPhone was picking up what she was saying so I tried to ensure I reiterated most of what she was saying. Disneyland is pushing hard to reopen. It’ll be interesting to see what happens as this is the first time in Disneyland history that the park has been shut down for such an extensive period of time.

node.text:
This is totally outside of the typical content I create and post, but I felt so strongly that this specific scene in the Netflix documentary Schitts Creek Best Wishes, Warmest Regards needed to be shared. Forgive me, you can hear me sniffling and crying as I filmed this. Schitts Creek is one of my favorite shows and has served as a super catalyst for acceptance, love, and positive personification of the LGBTQ+ community. I share some of my own thoughts and feelings (not very eloquently bc I had a hard time NOT crying) after the scene. I absolutely love that I am seeing more and more support LGBTQ+ community, but I also experience a devastating amount of hate on a daily basis. My goal behind our social media has been and will continue to be to offer ppl a small glimpse into our lives as a family in the hopes that we might open a few minds and hearts along the way. Love is love ❤️ And I hope and pray we see more and more queer representation in movies, television shows, books, etc. 🏳️‍🌈✊🏽 @schittscreek @instadanjlevy @annefrances 
.
.

node.text: I risked my life for some hand sanny today and met a T-Rex in the process. I am so so thankful for the generosity of these complete strangers ❤️ I’m a front line worker and have NO hand sanitizer. They reached out to me and we met at the Target on Harbor Blvd. near Disneyland! Keep spreading kindness, y’all!

node.text:
Missing our annual passes so much! Single days in Disneyland leave us feeling like we miss out on so many things we wish we could squeeze in. Character interactions were one of our favorite pastimes in the parks! The cost of going monthly is too much for many of us. Our weekly visits were the best part of our weeks prior to COVID. I know we’re not the only ones waiting for those AP’s to hit. Keeping our fingers crossed 🤞🏽

I think ppl expect to see immediate movement and that’s just not how it works, y’all. I know I posted our YouTube banner video yesterday and had ppl saying they were wondering if/when I was going go have it reworked. Not to mention alllllllll the ppl in my comments section asking prior to that. Things just take time. I’m still working and there are a zillion things that need to be done for all my kids. But we are def looking into adult adoptions and I’m hoping we are able to get it done for free since she aged out of foster care a couple years ago. Hopefully this answers the many, MANY questions I’ve received about this 😊

This video is an actual representation of why I made a BIG decision today (I was trying to work when this happened). I did something I never thought I’d do…I submitted my resignation to my supervisor. Long story short, I was being put in the position of having to choose between getting my children the kind of medical care the absolutely need or work. My kids will ALWAYS come first! Sadly, I think many families face the same work-life imbalance. That being said, I will be focusing on social media full time! That means I get to be home with my children, attend all of their appointments, be there for school events (and help in Evan and Eli’s special Ed classes), and be the kind of mom my kids deserve 😊 You can peep 👀 our stories for more info! I can’t wait to start creating content with more intention AND with my favorite people in the world! 🎉

Oh and for those wondering, Evan is fine 😁 He’s currently prancing around in his bathing suit about to go to the pool with sister, baby, and Jamari 👍🏽
